Job Description:
Perform logical and physical database design and creation, changes or removal of database, provide technical consultancy and advice on the usage of database software, advise application developers and owners on optimisation of database usage, SQL code and monitor availability of database, listener and other related processes;
review all daily logs, database alerts, database export logs, scheduled job logs;
perform database backups at frequency and within the timeframe as specified;
perform database recovery within the timeframe as defined; and
perform annual database recovery test on selected databases as determined.
develop, review, test, implement and monitor database backup and recovery jobs, procedures and schedules.

Job Highlights
Positive & Supportive Work Environment
Benefits & Welfare
Short walking distance from MRT
Job Description
Responsible for the company's database construction, migration, upgrade, maintenance, etc.;
Backup and restore the database, monitor and optimize the performance of the database;
Control user access to the database;
Formulate database development specifications and write specification documents.

Job Highlights
Positive & Supportive Work Environment
Benefits & Welfare
Short walking distance from MRT
Job Description
Responsible for the company's database construction, migration, upgrade, maintenance, etc.;
Backup and restore the database, monitor and optimize the performance of the database;
Control user access to the database;
Formulate database development specifications and write specification documents.

Job Responsibilities:
1. Responsible for the database and strong related components of the technical standards, media specifications and upgrades, installation and deployment and tuning, performance testing and improvement, event follow-up and processing;
2. Responsible for installing, upgrading and optimizing database server (including Oracle, MySQL, Greenplum), and application tools;
3. Responsible for database design system storage program, and develop future storage requirements plan;
4. Responsible for database backup, recovery strategy program development and implementation, database capacity design, to ensure that the database system security, integrity and operational efficiency;

