Responsible for the IT service of infrastructure, network, systems storage and backup in fulfilling business strategic goals as well as needs and meeting project deliverables;
Manage and contribute to the IT enterprise architect, design, evaluation, and deployment of IT systems covering network equipment, IT services, software application, messaging and collaboration technologies, etc.;
Responsible for the smooth operations of all ICT systems from desktop/laptop management, infrastructure and networking, support to communication (LAN, WAN,email, etc.), anti-virus, database, backup & disaster recovery system, regulatory and security compliance;
Responsible for the day-to-day operations of ICT including performance, integrity andsecurity, reporting service levels, tracking of IT operational metric, database (includingplanning, development and troubleshooting), data integrity, anti-virus/anti-spamprotection;
Formulate, develop, implement and enforce IT related policies, processes, guidelines, IT operation procedures, and standards for compliance and protect IT computer networks (computer work stations, computer servers, printers, wireless systems etc.) and application systems (online, database etc.) against computer intrusions, unauthorized access, and other malicious misuses to meet ISO9001 requirements and industry best practices;

